just from academic interest: They knew that the KLS factor encapsulates a world of information about how random processes behave within a convex shape. That’s because the smaller the best cut is, the harder it is for a random process to spread around the shape quickly.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>Think of a dumbbell, with two massive balls connected by a narrow bridge. The fact that you can divide it into two equal pieces with just a small cut precisely captures the notion that the bridge is a bottleneck. A heat source or a random walker in one of the two balls will usually take a long time to reach the other ball, since it has to find its way through the bottleneck.\u003c/p>\n","fadein":false,"__typename":"ACFContent"},"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6":{"hide_this_component":null,"acf_fc_layout":"image_component","layout":"inline","settings":"","attribution":"\u003cp>Samuel Velasco/Quanta Magazine\u003c/p>\n","caption":"","mobile_comp_caption":"","mobile_comp_attribution":"","sets":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0","typename":"ImageSet"}],"__typename":"ACFImageComponent"},"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0":{"settings":"","image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0.image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0.mobile_image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_caption":"","mobile_attribution":"","zoom_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0.zoom_image","typename":"Image"},"zoom_caption":"","zoom_attribution":"","mobile_zoom_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0.mobile_zoom_image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_zoom_caption":"","mobile_zoom_attribution":"","external_link":"","__typename":"ImageSet"},"$Post:100782.acf.modules.6.sets.0.image":{"alt":"","caption":"","url":"https://d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net/uploads/2021/03/KLS-Smallest-cut.svg","width":0,"height":0,"sizes":{"type":"